 🧩 Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock (Single Transaction)
🧠 Intuition

We need to maximize profit by buying once and selling once.

👉 Key idea:

Track the minimum price so far
Calculate profit at each step
🐢 Brute Force Approach
Try all pairs (i, j) where j > i
Track maximum profit
Code
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
    int n = prices.size();
    int maxProfit = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
            int profit = prices[j] - prices[i];
            maxProfit = max(maxProfit, profit);
        }
    }

    return maxProfit;
}
⚡ Better Approach (if any)
No need → directly optimal
🚀 Optimal Approach (Greedy)
Maintain:
minPrice → lowest so far
maxProfit → best profit
Code
#include <vector>
#include <climits>
using namespace std;

int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
    int minPrice = INT_MAX;
    int maxProfit = 0;

    for (int price : prices) {
        if (price < minPrice) {
            minPrice = price;
        } else {
            maxProfit = max(maxProfit, price - minPrice);
        }
    }

    return maxProfit;
}
⏱ Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
